		<section name="Ubuntu-tweedFeed">
			<subsection name="Introduction">
				<p>
					This is a small java app which sent notifiction to ubuntu-gnome-lib-notify from a Twitter search.
				</p>
				<p>You must compile it on Ubuntu and have libjava-gnome-java installed : </p>
				<code>sudo apt-get install libjava-gnome-java</code>
			</subsection>
			<subsection name="usage">
			    <p>Notify on a hashtag : </p>
				<code>java -jar Ubuntu-tweedFeed-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar -Dmyvar=#snow n</code>
				<p>Notify on an account : </p>
				<code>java -jar Ubuntu-tweedFeed-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar -Dmyvar=@BillGates n</code>
				<p>Use a proxy without authentication</p>
				<code>java -Dhttp.proxyHost=proxy.mordor.com -Dhttp.proxyPort=3128 -jar Ubuntu-tweedFeed-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar -Dmyvar=#snow n</code>
				<p>Usse a proxy with authentication</p>
				<code>java -Dhttp.proxyHost=proxy.mordor.com -Dhttp.proxyPort=3128 -jar Ubuntu-tweedFeed-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar -Dmyvar=#snow y loggin passwd</code>
			</subsection>
		</section>
